  "texts": [
    "5) Evaluation: Extensive synthetic and empirical experiments showing benefits of diagonal scaling.",
    "Autoscaling has been studied across distributed databases, cloud infrastructure, and serverless systems, but existing approaches treat horizontal and vertical scaling independently.",
    "A. Horizontal Scaling in Distributed DatabasesGoogle Spanner [6], Bigtable [3], Cassandra [11], Cock-roachDB [4], and DynamoDB [7] rely heavily on scaleout.",
    "Scaling horizontally improves parallelism but increases coordination costs.",
    "Spanner uses Paxos and TrueTime-based coordination; CockroachDB uses Raft; Cassandra uses eventually consistent replication.Horizontal scaling causes:• more messaging per consensus round,• larger replica groups,• greater replication fan-out,• increased leadership churn,• more rebalancing.Coordination overhead grows superlinearly in some cases [2], causing p99 latency to degrade even when average latency improves."
  ],
